messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

Files containing the handler implementations for user_api (relative to project root)

- app/api/cms/user.py

Explanation
- I searched the codebase for occurrences of user_api and found the blueprint defined in app/api/cms/user.py (it contains the line user_api = Blueprint("user", __name__)).
- That same file defines the route handlers (via @user_api.route) for the /user blueprint, including endpoints such as:
  - POST /register
  - POST /login
  - PUT /         (update)
  - PUT /change_password
  - GET /information
  - GET /refresh
  - GET /permissions
  - GET|POST /captcha
- The app/api/cms/__init__.py imports user_api from app.api.cms.user and registers it under the /user prefix, so the implementations are located in the file above.
- I ignored tests and focused only on the implementation files.
